devdoc.details: Inherits from OpenZeppelin's ERC721 for NFT functionality.

getLastTokenId().details: Returns the last token ID that was minted.

returns._0: The current value of the token ID counter, which corresponds to the last minted token ID.

mintNFT(address).details: Increments the `_tokenIds` counter, mints the NFT to the `recipient` address, and returns the new token ID.

params.recipient: The address of the recipient to whom the NFT will be minted.

returns._0: newItemId The token ID of the newly minted NFT.

devdoc.title: Example  NFT Minter

constructor.notice: Initializes the contract by setting a name and symbol for the NFT

getLastTokenId().notice: Retrieves the current value of the token ID counter.

mintNFT(address).notice: Mints a new NFT to the specified recipient address.

userdoc.notice: This contract demonstrates an NFT minting process that is not gated.
